caption: Table 4. Correlations of HRV Parameters Obtained by the Autoregression Technique with Interbeat Interval (IBI), Pre- Ejection Period (PEP), and Baroreflex Sensitivity (BRS) in the Physical Exercise Study (cf. Table 2) by Martín-Vázquez and Reyes del Paso (2010; Panel A, n = 40) and in the Chronic Pain Study by Reyes del Paso, Garrido, et al. (2010; Panel B, n = 64)
notes: Panel A and Panel B are sub-group header rows; other columns in those rows are empty. IBI-BL and IBI-Task rows have empty IBI column because correlation of IBI with itself is not reported. * denotes statistical significance; + (superscript) denotes marginal significance. Note at bottom: BL = baseline, Task = mental arithmetic, VLF = very low frequency, LF = low frequency, HF = high frequency.
